  - m_Id: 90485788672
    m_Localized: "<color=#610078><align=left><size=60>Application for Registration</size></align></color>\r\n\r\nEmployers
      have a legal responsibility to request and sign the registration of their employees
      in the Special Employment System for Domestic Workers. This obligation extends
      to the submission and signing of resignations and data variations related to
      the employment status of the staff.\r\n\r\nEmployers are required to request
      and sign the registration, resignation, and variations of data for their employees.
      If this obligation is not fulfilled, the employee may directly request their
      affiliation with the General Treasury of Social Security (TGSS).\r\n\r\nThis
      must be requested at the General Treasury of Social Security offices, in advance
      of the start of the work activity.\r\n\r\nThe resignation request and data
      variations must be submitted within 3 calendar days following the cessation
      of work or the date on which the variation occurs, through the Import@ss platform.\r\n\r\n<color=#610078><align=left><size=60>Import@ss</size></align></color>\r\n\r\nRegistering
      a person in the Special Employment System for Domestic Workers is easier than
      ever thanks to Import@ss, the new portal of the General Treasury of Social
      Security (TGSS) that allows you to complete the process in just 9 steps without
      having to provide documentation, although you will need to have a series of
      data prepared. You can do this anytime, from any computer or mobile device
      with an internet connection.\r\n\r\nYou can access Import@ss directly from
      this link or from the access points enabled on the website, the electronic
      headquarters, and the Social Security mobile application. To request registration,
      you must identify yourself using the following methods:\r\n\r\n\u25CF Electronic
      certificate\r\n\r\n\u25CF Cl@ve\r\n\r\n\u25CF Via SMS\r\n\r\n<color=blue><align=left><u><link=https://portal.seg-social.gob.es/wps/portal/importass/importass>https://portal.seg-social.gob.es/wps/portal/importass/importass</link></u></align></color>\r\n\r\nSo
      far, employment relationships in the domestic sector have represented a high
      percentage of in-person processing and difficulties in digital processing,
      as they could require up to three additional procedures to the registration
      itself if the worker and/or the employer do not have a Social Security Number
      (NUSS) and the employer does not have a Contribution Account Code (CCC).\r\n\r\nIn
      Import@ss, the process adapts to the user's circumstances, creating the Social
      Security Number and the Contribution Account Code if necessary. The process
      is designed so that the user, from the public or personal area, can complete
      a registration in a single flow with a maximum of 9 steps, divided by the type
      of information requested from the user.\r\n\r\n<color=#610078><align=left><size=60>Steps
      to Register</size></align></color>\r\n\r\nOnce you have accessed the domestic
      employment registration service in Import@ss and identified yourself or accessed
      your personal area, you must first indicate whether you are processing the
      registration as an employer or as a worker. The system will give you the option
      to process a new registration or continue with one you have previously started.\r\n\r\nNext,
      you simply need to fill out the 9 steps in which clarity of information, ease
      of use, control over each of the steps, and security of the process stand out:\r\n\r\n1.
      Employee's data: Type and number of identification document (DNI or NIE) and
      date of birth.\r\n\r\n2. Employer's data: Indicate whether the employee will
      care for a large family. If you meet the conditions, you may be entitled to
      a bonus.\r\n\r\n3. Duration of the contract: Indicate the start date of the
      activity and the type of contract (indefinite or fixed-term).\r\n\r\n4. Work
      schedule and salary: You must mark whether the contract is full-time or hourly,
      the number of hours worked per week/month, how the salary payment has been
      agreed (monthly or weekly), the salary they will receive, whether they will
      receive a salary during vacations, whether extra payments are included, whether
      guard hours will be worked, or if payment in kind has been agreed (the system
      will inform you of the fee to be paid based on this data). Remember that the
      salary must be at least equal to the SMI (if it is full-time).\r\n\r\n5. Activity
      address: Fill in the details or select the activity address if it matches any
      of those registered in the TGSS database.\r\n\r\n6. Insurer: Select the insurance
      entity, choosing between the INSS or a collaborating Mutual.\r\n\r\n7. Contact
      information: Enter the contact details as the domestic employer.\r\n\r\n8.
      Bank account: You must provide the account where the corresponding monthly
      fee will be charged.\r\n\r\n9. Review your data: Import@ss will offer you a
      summary of all fields, which you can modify if you detect any errors.\r\n\r\nSteps
      may be omitted if the TGSS already has the corresponding information.\r\n\r\nIf
      the data is correct, you must give your consent after reading and accepting
      the responsible declaration by marking the corresponding box. Once done, you
      can proceed to sign the request and request registration; the system will show
      you a receipt and offer you the option to download the supporting documentation
      in PDF format.\r\n\r\nLink to explanatory video of the step-by-step process:
      \r\n\r\n<color=blue><align=left><u><link=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WX2fshb4dPk>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WX2fshb4dPk</link></u></align></color>\r\n\r\nWithout
      identification method\r\n\r\nIf you do not have any of the previous identification
      methods, you can use the request submission service on the portal, where you
      can request registration using this form without prior identification. You
      can also process resignations and modifications of data.\r\n\r\nTo process
      the registration, you must complete and attach:\r\n\r\n1. Employer's data:
      personal details, address, Contribution Account Code (CCC), banking details
      for fee collection, copy of identification document.\r\n\r\n2. Employee's data:
      personal details, copy of identification document, and Social Security Number
      (NUSS).\r\n\r\n3. Labor relationship data (number of hours worked, salary,
      start date of the labor relationship, whether there are any payments in kind,
      overnight stays, etc.).\r\n\r\n4. The employment contract.\r\n\r\n<color=blue><align=left><u><link=https://www.sepe.es/HomeSepe/empresas/Contratos-de-trabajo/modelos-contrato.html>https://www.sepe.es/HomeSepe/empresas/Contratos-de-trabajo/modelos-contrato.html</link></u></align></color>\r\n\r\n5.
      The registration forms for Social Security.\r\n\r\n<color=blue><align=left><u><link=https://tinyurl.com/4b7xdkar>https://tinyurl.com/4b7xdkar</link></u></align></color>\r\n\r\n6.
      If this is the first time you are hiring a domestic employee, you must also
      submit Model TA.6-0138 HOGAR Request for Contribution Account Code.\r\n\r\n<color=blue><align=left><u><link=https://tinyurl.com/57pxkr6s>https://tinyurl.com/57pxkr6s</link></u></align></color>\r\n\r\n7.
      Additionally, if the employee does not have a Social Security affiliation number,
      it should be processed using Model TA 1.\r\n\r\n<color=blue><align=left><u><link=https://www.seg-social.es/wps/portal/wss/internet/Trabajadores/Afiliacion/10817/31190/572>https://www.seg-social.es/wps/portal/wss/internet/Trabajadores/Afiliacion/10817/31190/572</link></u></align></color>\r\n\r\nTo
      guide you through the process, you can use the virtual assistant available
      on the website and in the Electronic Headquarters of Social Security. It will
      show you the steps to follow, the necessary requirements, and links to the
      electronic headquarters for submitting requests.\r\n\r\n<color=#610078><align=left><size=60>Deadlines</size></align></color>\r\n\r\nIn
      any of the previous cases, registration must be processed before the start
      of the work activity, with a maximum advance of 60 days, and it is the responsibility
      of the employer, just like the payment of contributions.\r\n\r\nRemember that,
      since January 1, 2023, it is no longer possible to agree with domestic workers
      who perform less than 60 hours of work per month per employer to assume the
      obligations regarding contributions, affiliation, and registration in Social
      Security, as could be done until now, after the entry into force of some of
      the novelties of Royal Decree-Law 16/2022, of September 6, which improves working
      conditions for this group, including unemployment protection.\r\n\r\n<color=#610078><align=left><size=60>Essential
      Elements and Forms of the Contract</size></align></color>\r\n\r\n\u25CF Orally:
      contracts shorter than four weeks (at any time, it can be required that it
      be formalized in writing).\r\n\r\n\u25CF In writing: contracts lasting four
      weeks or more.\r\n\r\nThe contract must be made in writing, with one copy for
      the employer and another for the employee. It is important to do this because
      if the contract is not formalized in writing, it is presumed that the employment
      relationship is indefinite and full-time.\r\n\r\n<color=blue><align=left><u><link=https://www.mites.gob.es/es/portada/serviciohogar/nueva-regulacion/contratacion/index.htm>https://www.mites.gob.es/es/portada/serviciohogar/nueva-regulacion/contratacion/index.htm</link></u></align></color>\r\n\r\nWhen
      the duration of the contract is more than four weeks, the worker must receive
      information about the essential elements of the contract if they are not included
      in the written contract formalized, which, in addition to general aspects (identification
      of the parties, salary, working hours, etc.), will include:\r\n\r\n\u25CF Salary
      payments in kind, when their existence has been agreed upon.\r\n\r\n\u25CF
      Payments in kind must be specifically valued, detailing the amount and frequency
      of the remuneration.\r\n\r\nThe written contract must also specify the following
      information:\r\n\r\n\u25CF Employment start date, with reference to whether
      it is indefinite or temporary.\r\n\r\n\u25CF The work schedule (the hours and
      days of the week that the worker will perform their duties).\r\n\r\n\u25CF
      The maximum number of working hours, as well as the specific duties to be carried
      out by the employee.\r\n\r\nLastly, it\u2019s advisable to keep a record of
      all the communications with the employee, whether by email or message, to avoid
      any misunderstandings or disputes.\r\n\r\n<color=#610078><align=left><size=60>Rights
      and Obligations</size></align></color>\r\n\r\nThe employer must comply with
      their obligations regarding the employee, including the timely payment of salary
      and contributions to the Social Security system.\r\n\r\nThe employee has the
      right to a fair salary and to receive the agreed payment on time. They also
      have the right to a safe and healthy work environment.\r\n\r\nFor any conflicts
      that arise, both parties should try to resolve the issue amicably before considering
      legal action. If necessary, they can contact labor inspectors or seek legal
      advice.\r\n\r\n<color=#610078><align=left><size=60>Contact Information</size></align></color>\r\n\r\nIf
      you have any questions or need further assistance, you can contact the General
      Treasury of Social Security at:\r\n\r\nPhone: 901 50 20 50 or 91 22 88 300\r\n\r\nEmail:
      consultas@seg-social.es\r\n\r\nRemember that keeping open communication with
      your employee and ensuring clarity in the work relationship is key to avoiding
      misunderstandings and fostering a good work environment.\r\n\r\n"
