  - m_Id: 607702192128
    m_Localized: '<color=#610078><align=left><size=60>Salary Table and Contribution
      Bases</size></align></color>



      <color=#610078><align=left><size=60>A.
      Salary Table of the Domestic Employment Regime</size></align></color>



      The
      salary will be agreed upon by the employer and the employee, always guaranteeing
      the Minimum Interprofessional Wage (SMI) on an annual basis in proportion to
      the hours worked. The SMI must always be paid in cash, and deductions for in-kind
      benefits that result in the cash salary being less than the SMI are not allowed.

'
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 756675481600
    m_Localized: 'In the internal regime, the domestic worker will be entitled to
      receive the SMI (in cash) and a salary in kind that will cover maintenance
      and accommodation in the home (single room, basic meals, personal hygiene,
      use of the washing machine, etc.).



      The worker who works full-time,
      under the internal regime or part-time, is entitled to receive two extraordinary
      payments in the amount agreed upon by the parties, while always guaranteeing
      the receipt of the SMI (in cash) on an annual basis in proportion to the hours
      worked.



      <color=#610078><align=left><size=60>B. Contribution Base Scale
      (from January 2024)</size></align></color>



      Contribution bases are
      determined based on the monthly remuneration of the domestic worker, following
      established brackets to ensure a fair contribution to the Social Security system.

'
