  - m_Id: 848815951872
    m_Localized: "<color=#610078><size=60>C. Applicable bonuses in the special Employment
      of Home system.</size></color>\r\n\r\nThe following are some of the basic bonuses
      applicable in the Special Employment of Home System:\r\n\r\n\u25CF Reduction
      for registration in the regime of 20% on the employer's contribution to Social
      Security for common contingencies.\r\n\r\n\u25CF Benefit of 45% on the employer's
      contribution to Social Security for common contingencies for hiring caregivers
      in large families (not cumulative with the 20% registration reduction). In
      any case, this bonus will only be applicable for the hiring of a single caregiver
      for each family unit officially recognized as a large family.\r\n\r\nOnly employers
      who are up to date with their payment obligations to Social Security at the
      time of granting can obtain reductions, bonuses, or any other benefit regarding
      the bases, rates, and contributions of Social Security and for joint collection
      concepts.\r\n\r\n<color=#610078><align=left><size=60>D. Benefits for workers
      who contribute to Social Security.</size></align></color>\r\n\r\nWe must highlight
      the benefits obtained by workers who contribute to Social Security:\r\n\r\n\u25CF
      Contributions to Social Security: These contributions support the social protection
      of the worker, including aspects such as retirement, disability, illness, and
      maternity.\r\n\r\n\u25CF Access to unemployment benefits: Domestic workers
      have the right to access unemployment benefits if they lose their job.\r\n\r\n\u25CF
      Protection for workplace accidents and occupational diseases: If a domestic
      worker suffers an accident related to their work or develops an occupational
      disease, they will have the right to receive medical assistance and a leave
      of absence as determined by the professional doctor.\r\n\r\n\u25CF Protection
      in cases of maternity and paternity: Protection is provided in cases of maternity,
      granting economic benefits to domestic workers who are on maternity leave.\r\n\r\n\u25CF
      Inclusion in the pension system: This allows domestic workers to accumulate
      rights to receive a pension upon retirement.\r\n\r\nSOURCES:\r\n\r\n<color=blue><u><link=https://www.mites.gob.es/es/portada/serviciohogar/preguntas-frecuentes/retribuciones/index.htm>https://www.mites.gob.es/es/portada/serviciohogar/preguntas-frecuentes/retribuciones/index.htm</link>\r\n\r\n<link=https://www.seg-social.es/wps/portal/wss/internet/Trabajadores/CotizacionRecaudacionTrabajadores/36537#36556>https://www.seg-social.es/wps/portal/wss/internet/Trabajadores/CotizacionRecaudacionTrabajadores/36537#36556</link>\r\n\r\n<link=https://www.seg-social.es/wps/portal/wss/internet/Trabajadores/CotizacionRecaudacionTrabajadores/10721/10957/9932/2288>https://www.seg-social.es/wps/portal/wss/internet/Trabajadores/CotizacionRecaudacionTrabajadores/10721/10957/9932/2288</link>\r\n\r\n<link=https://qido.es/blog/nuevo-salario-minimo-interprofesional-smi-en-el-regimen-de-empleadas-de-hogar-2024/>https://qido.es/blog/nuevo-salario-minimo-interprofesional-smi-en-el-regimen-de-empleadas-de-hogar-2024/</link></u></color>\r\n"
