    m_Localized: "<color=#610078></align=left><size=60>Unemployment</color></size></align>\r\n\r\nThe
      **Royal Decree-Law 16/2022**, of September 6, aimed at improving the working
      conditions and Social Security of household employees, aligns their conditions
      with those of other workers. It establishes that unemployment benefits are
      now part of the protective measures for household employees within the special
      system.\r\n\r\nFrom **October 1, 2022**, unemployment contributions became
      mandatory for household employees. As of **January 2023**, contributions are
      calculated based on the General State Budget Law.\r\n\r\nHousehold employees
      can be considered legally unemployed if their employment is terminated through
      a written communication from the employer, clearly stating:\r\n\r\n\u25CF The
      employer's decision to terminate the employment relationship.\r\n\u25CF The
      reason for the termination.\r\n\r\n<color=#610078></align=left><size=60>When
      Can I Apply for Unemployment Benefits?</color></size></align>\r\n\r\nYou must
      submit the application **within 15 business days** from the last day worked.
      The application can be submitted through:\r\n\r\n\u25CF SEPE's electronic headquarters\r\n\u25CF
      In-person at a benefits office (appointment required via SEPE's electronic
      headquarters or phone)\r\n\u25CF At any public registration office\r\n\u25CF
      By administrative mail\r\n\r\nIf you submit the unemployment benefit application
      after the deadline, your entitlement will begin from the date of the application,
      and you will lose the days that have passed between the initial entitlement
      and the submission date.\r\n\r\nIn cases where the employment is terminated,
      the worker can appeal the employer's decision. If you did not submit your application
      within the initial deadline, you will have a new 15-day period starting from
      the conciliation act or from the court decision.\r\n\r\nSEPE must issue a resolution
      within 15 days of the application submission and notify you within 10 days
      after the decision is made.\r\n\r\n<color=#610078></align=left><size=60>Have
      I Worked More or Less Than a Year?</color></size></align>\r\n\r\nFor additional
      information, you can consult the following links depending on whether you have
      worked more or less than a year:\r\n\r\n\u25CF **More than a year:**  \r\n<color=blue></align=left><u><link=https://www.sepe.es/HomeSepe/Personas/distributiva-prestaciones/quiero-cobrar-el-paro/he-trabajado-mas-de-un-ano.html>https://www.sepe.es/HomeSepe/Personas/distributiva-prestaciones/quiero-cobrar-el-paro/he-trabajado-mas-de-un-ano.html</link></u></color></align=left>\r\n\r\n\u25CF
      **Less than a year:**  \r\n<color=blue></align=left><u><link=https://www.sepe.es/HomeSepe/Personas/distributiva-prestaciones/quiero-cobrar-el-paro/he-trabajado-menos-un-ano.html>https://www.sepe.es/HomeSepe/Personas/distributiva-prestaciones/quiero-cobrar-el-paro/he-trabajado-menos-un-ano.html</link></u></color></align=left>\r\n\r\n<color=#610078></align=left><size=60>How
      to Apply for Unemployment Benefits?</color></size></align>\r\n\r\n**Step 1:
      Access Applications**\r\n\r\n1. Go to SEPE's online services portal\r\n2. Click
      on the \"Access Applications\" button to view the available types of applications\r\n3.
      Use an authentication and digital signature method (Cl@ve, Digital Certificate,
      or DNIe)\r\n\r\n**Step 2: Type of Applications**\r\n\r\n1. Select the type
      of application that matches your situation: initial registration, resumption,
      labor compatibility options\u2026\r\n2. Carefully review each option and choose
      the one that fits your case\r\n\r\n**Step 3: Attachments to Applications**\r\n\r\n1.
      Once the application is selected, review the available sections and subsections\r\n2.
      Ensure all personal information is correct and complete additional fields if
      necessary\r\n3. Read the legal texts and the obligations associated with the
      application\r\n\r\n**Step 4: Application Confirmation**\r\n\r\n1. Sign the
      application using one of the available accreditation methods (Cl@ve, Digital
      Certificate, or DNIe)\r\n2. Follow the specific instructions for each signature
      method\r\n3. Verify that the signature process has been completed successfully\r\n\r\n**Step
      5: Signature of the Application**\r\n\r\n1. After signing the application,
      download and print a receipt for your records\r\n2. Review all the additional
      information provided regarding the obligations as a beneficiary\r\n3. Stay
      informed about the status of your application and any future communication
      from SEPE\r\n\r\n*Link to the Ministry of Labor and Social Economy on unemployment
      benefits*  \r\n<color=blue></align=left><u><link=https://tinyurl.com/48v7r8u4>https://tinyurl.com/48v7r8u4*</link></u></color></align=left>\r\n"
